OC is absent. By comparing calculations where SOC in switched off vs. switched\non in ncDFT calculations, we find that SOC consistently reduces the pumped spin\ncurrent and, therefore, the effective SMC.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 May 2019 17:58:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 24 Dec 2019 03:23:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-04"}
